    "value": "To set up Claude Code Channels (Telegram and Discord integration) and configure the channels settings, follow these steps and best practices summarized from leading guides:\n\n### Prerequisites (Must-Do Before Setup)\n- **Claude Code version:** v2.1.80 or later. Check by running `claude --version`.\n- **Bun runtime:** Claude Channel plugins are Bun scripts; Node.js won't work. Install Bun if needed (`curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash`).\n- **claude.ai authentication:** ONLY `claude.ai login` works for Channels, not API key or Console login.\n- **Admin enablement (Team/Enterprise):** An admin must enable Channels under Claude Code settings in the organization portal before setup for any member will work【3:0†source】【3:1†source】【3:4†source】【3:7†source】.\n\n---\n\n### Step-by-Step Setup for Telegram\n1. **Create a Telegram Bot:**\n   - Open Telegram, message @BotFather, send `/newbot`, follow prompts, and copy the token.\n\n2. **Install the Plugin:**\n   - In Claude Code terminal: \n     ```\n     /plugin install telegram@claude-plugins-official\n     ```\n     If you get a \"not found\" error, run \n     ```\n     /plugin marketplace add anthropics/claude-plugins-official\n     ```\n     and then try again.\n\n3. **Configure the Token:**\n   - Run: \n     ```\n     /telegram:configure \u003ctoken\u003e\n     ```\n   - This saves the token to `~/.claude/channels/telegram/.env`. Alternatively, set the `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` environment variable【3:1†source】【3:7†source】.\n\n4. **Restart Claude with Channels:**\n   - Exit and relaunch, explicitly naming your channel plugin with `--channels`:\n     ```\n     claude --channels plugin:telegram@claude-plugins-official\n     ```\n   - **Important:** The `--channels` flag is required every session.\n\n5. **Pair Your Telegram Account:**\n   - Message your bot. The bot replies with a pairing code.\n   - In Claude, run: `/telegram:access pair \u003ccode\u003e`\n   - (Recommended) Limit access to yourself: `/telegram:access policy allowlist`\n\n---\n\n### Step-by-Step Setup for Discord\n- The Discord process is analogous: create a Discord bot, install the Discord plugin, configure with your bot token, and launch Claude with the correct `--channels` flag.\n- You may need to configure additional permissions and add your bot to Discord servers as required by Discord's bot API.\n\n---\n\n### Practical Configuration and Security Tips\n- You can enable multiple channels with a space-separated list after `--channels`.\n- Keep sessions running in `tmux` or `screen` for persistent background access.\n- Only those paired or on your allowlist can message/command your bot; always switch to allowlist mode after setup for security.\n- All channel/plugin credentials and config files are saved under `~/.claude/channels/`【3:6†source】【3:7†source】.\n\n---\n\n### Advanced Configuration (Settings Files and Hierarchy)\n- System-wide, user, project, and local settings can be managed via JSON files:\n  - `~/.claude/settings.json` (user global)\n  - `.claude/settings.json` (project, shared via git)\n  - `.claude/settings.local.json` (personal, project-specific)\n- Managed/organizational settings (for Enterprise/Team) may be deployed by IT under `/etc/claude-code/` (Linux) or `/Library/Application Support/ClaudeCode/` (macOS).\n- Settings precedence: managed \u003e CLI arguments \u003e local project \u003e shared project \u003e user【3:3†source】【3:6†source】【3:2†source】.\n\n---\n\n### In Summary:\n1. Install the right Claude Code and Bun versions.\n2. Set up your bot (Telegram/Discord).\n3. Install the official channel plugin and configure it.\n4. Launch with the `--channels` flag.\n5. Pair and secure your bot.\n6. Use settings files to control permissions, environment, and organizational settings.\n\n**For detailed commands, flows, and troubleshooting, see:**\n- [Lowcode Agency Telegram/Discord Setup Guide](https://www.lowcode.agency/blog/claude-code-channels-setup-telegram-discord)\n- [Official Claude Code Docs on Channels](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/channels)\n- [CAIO Comprehensive Settings Guide](https://www.thecaio.ai/blog/claude-code-settings-guide)\n- [DEV Community hands-on Telegram Walkthrough](https://dev.to/alanwest/claude-code-channels-control-your-ai-coding-agent-from-telegram-2b0n)【3:0†source】【3:1†source】【3:3†source】【3:7†source】【3:4†source】.\n\nIf you need specific config file examples, troubleshooting, or Discord bot additional details, let me know!",
